  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "There are several ways to check your Provident Fund (PF) balance in India:\n\n**1. Online through the EPFO Portal (Unified Member Portal):**\n\n*   **Prerequisites:**\n    *   UAN (Universal Account Number) activated.\n    *   Mobile number linked to UAN.\n    *   KYC (Know Your Customer) details (Aadhaar, PAN, Bank Account) updated and verified.\n\n*   **Procedure:**\n    1.  **Visit the EPFO Member Portal:** Go to the official EPFO website: `https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/memberinterface/`\n    2.  **Login:** Enter your UAN, password, and captcha code.\n    3.  **View Passbook:** After logging in, click on the \"View\" tab.  Then choose \"Passbook\" or \"Claim Status\".\n        *   **Passbook:** This option will show you your EPF passbook with details of contributions, interest earned, and withdrawals.  You may need to select the relevant member ID if you have multiple accounts.\n        *   **Claim Status:** This allows you to track the status of any claims you have filed.  This might also indirectly show a balance.\n\n*   **Note:** The passbook is usually updated a few hours or days after contributions are made.\n\n**2. Through UMANG App:**\n\n*   **Prerequisites:**\n    *   UAN activated.\n    *   Mobile number linked to UAN.\n\n*   **Procedure:**\n    1.  **Download and Install:** Download and install the UMANG (Unified Mobile Application for New-age Governance) app from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n    2.  **Register/Login:** Register with your mobile number and complete the OTP verification.\n    3.  **Search for EPFO:** Search for \"EPFO\" within the app.\n    4.  **Employee Centric Services:** Select \"Employee Centric Services\".\n    5.  **View Passbook:** Click on \"View Passbook\".\n    6.  **Enter UAN:** Enter your UAN and an OTP will be sent to your registered mobile number.\n    7.  **View Passbook:** Enter the OTP and view your EPF passbook.\n\n**3. Through SMS:**\n\n*   **Prerequisites:**\n    *   UAN activated.\n    *   Mobile number linked to UAN.\n\n*   **Procedure:**\n    1.  **Send SMS:** Send an SMS to `7738299899` from your registered mobile number.  The SMS should be in the following format:\n        `EPFOHO UAN ENG`  (for English)\n        Replace `ENG` with the first three letters of your preferred language (e.g., HIN for Hindi, TAM for Tamil).\n    2.  **Receive SMS:** You will receive an SMS containing details of your latest PF contribution and balance.\n\n**4. Through Missed Call:**\n\n*   **Prerequisites:**\n    *   UAN activated.\n    *   Mobile number linked to UAN.\n    *   KYC details (Aadhaar, PAN, Bank Account) updated and verified.\n\n*   **Procedure:**\n    1.  **Give Missed Call:** Give a missed call to `011-22901406` from your registered mobile number.\n    2.  **Receive SMS:** You will receive an SMS containing details of your latest PF contribution and balance.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **UAN Activation:** The most crucial step is to activate your UAN (Universal Account Number).  You can do this on the EPFO member portal.  You will need your member ID (PF account number) which you can get from your employer.\n*   **KYC Update:** Ensure your KYC details (Aadhaar, PAN, Bank Account) are updated and verified with your UAN.  This is essential for accessing many of the online services and claiming your PF.\n*   **Registered Mobile Number:** All of the methods except the physical passbook rely on your mobile number being registered and linked with your UAN. Make sure your mobile number is active and up-to-date.\n*   **Security:** Be cautious of phishing scams.  Always access the EPFO portal through the official website link and never share your UAN, password, or OTP with anyone.\n\n**Troubleshooting:**\n\n*   **UAN Not Activated:**  If your UAN is not activated, you won't be able to check your balance online. Activate it through the EPFO portal.\n*   **Incorrect Credentials:**  Ensure you are entering your correct UAN and password.\n*   **Mobile Number Not Registered:** If your mobile number is not registered with EPFO, you'll need to update it through your employer.\n*   **Portal Issues:**  Sometimes the EPFO portal may experience technical issues. Try again later.\n*   **Delayed Updates:**  It may take some time for contributions to reflect in your passbook.\n\nIf you are having trouble checking your PF balance, contact your employer's HR department or the EPFO helpline for assistance.\n",
